item.title: Breast Cancer Survival Prediction
item.description: Dataset that has been used here is Seer Breast Cancer Data. This dataset of breast cancer patients was obtained from the 2017 November update of the SEER Program of the NCI, which provides information on population-based cancer statistics. The dataset involved female patients with infiltrating duct and lobular carcinoma breast cancer diagnosed in 2006-2010. Project Steps: Data Wrangling - This is where we try to get a raw understanding of what the data looks like and perform transformations and operations on it to bring it to a more usable state

Aspiring data scientist with a biomedical engineering degree and many years of software development experience. Recently I was involved in building a software service company for restaurants with a small team. This experience helped me in many ways, especially expanding my vision of problem solving and how to think out of the box. Also I was involved in designing the data models to improve the data collection processes and make sure we have all the necessary features for data analysis.
